<item>
            <title>[SPARK-6650] ExecutorAllocationManager never stops</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-6650</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;ExecutorAllocationManager&lt;/tt&gt; doesn&apos;t even have a stop() method. That means that when the owning SparkContext goes away, the internal thread it uses to schedule its activities remains alive.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That means it constantly spams the logs and does who knows what else that could affect any future contexts that are allocated.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s particularly evil during unit tests, since it slows down everything else after the suite is run, leaving multiple threads behind.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
